It has been reported that the lingering cold war at the Imo State House of Assembly, Owerri, has taken a new turn.  The crisis on Thursday, took another dimension as the lawmakers impeached their majority leader, Uche Ogbuagu. Ogbuagu, who represents Ikeduru state constituency, had defected to the All Progressives Congress from Peoples Democratic Party shortly after Emeka Ihedioha was removed in January 2020 by the supreme Court as governor in order to emerge a principal officer of the house. At the Thursday’s plenary which was held under tight security, Ogbuagu was removed by a majority vote. The speaker, Paul Emezim, who was presiding the plenary announced that the majority leader of the house had been impeached. The PUNCH gathered that the impeached majority leader had been having cold war with deputy speaker, Amarachi Iwuanyanwu. Details later…  Source The Imo state house of assembly on Thursday impeached its majority leader, Uche Ogbuagu. Ogbuagu represents Ikeduru state constituency was said to have been impeached by a majority vote. He had defected to the All Progressives Congress (APC) from People’s Democratic Party (PDP). Details later… Source In "Politics" Imo State House of Assembly has repealed the 2007 pension act which effectively stripped ex- governors , their deputies and ex- speakers of their pensions and privileges, Daily Sun reports. The executive bill is entitled, “A bill for a law to repeal the Imo State governors and Speakers Pension and… In "Politics" By Ugonne Uzoma Owerri - Speaker of the Imo House of Assembly, Dr Collins Chiji on Tuesday announced his defection from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to the All Progressives Congress (APC). Chiji who made the announcement during the plenary session of the house also announced the defection of seven… In "Politics"